/* Ethnic groups */ This table is highly misleading. Reading the original study, the "admixed population" they are referring to here was (intentionally) not representative -- it was about 50% Native American. "The figures are however not very high given that about half of the component of the admixed populations is Native American." https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3176197/

/* top */No official census data for European and Mestizo Argentines, unlike Indigenous and African ones that do have official numbers. I recommend stop using unofficial sources and estimates that vary a lot in their numbers for each ethnic group.

I clarified that Muslims, rather than having "different duties" than non-Muslims, were explicitly granted rights that non-Muslims were denied. The original was unclear in stating the inferior status of non-Muslims, and could be read as being Muslim as carrying a disadvantage rather than privilege. The source does not appear to support the claim that Muslims had "different rights," but rather explicitly states that non- Muslims' rights were restricted.
